 Nigerian BET award winner, Wizkid has chalked another milestone in his musical career. The ‘Soko’ hit maker has gained a staggering total of 1.7 billion music streams on music streaming platform, Spotify. The huge number of streams includes songs Wizkid has featured in. Furthermore, Wizkid has gained a total of 3 billion streams on Spotify, Apple Music, Youtube, SoundCloud Tidal and Deezer. In addition to his new achievement, the ‘Ojuelegba’ crooner has become the only African artist on the Spotify 100 most streamed artists worldwide list. Source